type Repeatable<T> = readonly [T, ...T[]];

const repeatableString: Repeatable<string> = ["hello", "world", "hello", "world"];
```

However, if you're looking for a more straightforward way to represent a type that can be repeated any number of times, you could use a generic type with a constraint:

```typescript
type Repeatable<T> = T[];

const repeatableString: Repeatable<string> = ["hello", "world", "hello", "world"];
```

Or, you could use a union type to represent a type that can be repeated any number of times:

```typescript
